Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.30,0:00:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously on\N"The Lost Symbol"...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is breakthrough stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And we may only be\Nscratching the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.18,0:00:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,BLAKE: Zachary Solomon died\Nin a prison riot in Turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.22,0:00:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-We need Langdon.\N-What about Peter Solomon?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.27,0:00:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,MAL'AKH (recording):\NPeter is in the borderland
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.48,0:00:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-between Heaven and Hell.\N-He might already be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.23,0:00:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-LANGDON: It's a piece of rock.\N-It's a map!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.44,0:00:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The pyramid and the capstone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.77,0:00:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,will reveal the location\Nof the portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.69,0:00:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hebrew... it's code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.15,0:00:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,LANGDON (voice-over):\NThe ring could contain\Nsome kind of decryption.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.49,0:00:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I am doing what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.91,0:00:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,MAL'AKH:\NYou were told to do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.91,0:00:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut her loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.66,0:00:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN:\NHey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.79,0:00:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you can't be in here, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Park's closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.42,0:00:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see some ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.80,0:00:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey!\N-(grunting)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.47,0:00:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-(gunshot)\N-(yells)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.31,0:00:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,(monitor beeping steadily)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.52,0:01:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors say his partner\Nshould make a full recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.32,0:01:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,SATO:\NToo early to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.32,0:01:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,NUÑEZ:\NI got sent 7,000 miles away\Nto fight extremists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.58,0:01:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't your fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.33,0:01:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a hole in my side\Nthat says otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.34,0:01:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Some evidence went missing\Nyesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.96,0:01:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Solomon's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.59,0:01:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You happen to know anything\Nabout that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.68,0:01:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.85,0:01:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying if--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.56,0:01:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothetically--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you were aiding\NLangdon and Katherine,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.81,0:01:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd only be putting them\Nin more danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.94,0:01:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't protect them\Nfrom the guy who did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.48,0:01:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry\Nabout me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.53,0:01:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done playing the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.78,0:01:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Made my wife a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.37,0:02:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.26,0:02:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-Home sweet home.\N-Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you make tostones, babe?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.85,0:02:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ZOE:\NI wouldn't get my hopes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.35,0:02:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.77,0:02:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\NWelcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey.\N-How you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.61,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.94,0:02:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I said you guys\Ncould set up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.49,0:02:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-to crack your Bible code,\Nnot eat all my food.\N-Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave you\Nto your new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-Maybe we should go.\N-No. She's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She's just worried about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I wouldn't go anywhere\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.09,0:02:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a lurker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.38,0:02:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Three houses down, north side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.85,0:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-He's found us.\N-No, it's Sato's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.77,0:03:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She came to the hospital\Nlooking for you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.60,0:03:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're wrong\Nand it's Mal'akh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone he sent, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.35,0:03:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would he do that?\NHe needs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.36,0:03:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Nothing, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.78,0:03:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bullshit me, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something\NI haven't told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.70,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He called when we were\Nat the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.33,0:03:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mal'akh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.84,0:03:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he made it very clear\Nthat he wants me doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.64,0:03:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.72,0:03:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-And you didn't tell me this\Nbefore?\N-I didn't want to scare you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOr maybe you agree with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.11,0:03:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you think you'd be\Nbetter off doing this alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-It's not about agreeing\Nwith him.\N-He has my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-It's about acknowledging the\Nvery real danger he presents.\N-I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:03:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a literal assassin...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what it's going\Nto take to get me to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bellamy, Ellison Blake,\NCentral Intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.57,0:04:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.61,0:04:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you put\Nyour time here to good use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Caught up on a little reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.91,0:04:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I miss books.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sci-fi-- that was my first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.50,0:04:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's not high art,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.00,0:04:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but the stakes--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.84,0:04:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how can you beat a story\Nabout the end of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.55,0:05:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get much time\Nto read anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.01,0:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.84,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's okay,\Nbecause I've come to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.85,0:05:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that the most\Ninteresting stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.18,0:05:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...are true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the sign\Nfor the Leviathan Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a secret sect\Nwithin the Freemasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.03,0:05:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to which you belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I also know that their purpose\Nis to protect
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.54,0:05:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,some very old,\Nvery valuable information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.13,0:05:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So my question for you is:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.59,0:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.55,0:05:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This portal\Nthat I've heard about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhat you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.10,0:05:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do know\Nthat you can't keep me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.15,0:05:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:05:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.70,0:06:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Any word on Langdon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet. Got people looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.87,0:06:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-What about him?\N-Mm, he's the quiet type.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.16,0:06:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he could use\Na change of scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.96,0:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Have him moved over\Nto Southwoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,LANGDON (quietly):\NAll right, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's an equation.\NMaybe an equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a...\NOr coordinates?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.27,0:06:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.89,0:06:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.27,0:06:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs) Ciphers...\NA Hill cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.98,0:06:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a Hill cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right here.\NIt's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(pencil tip snaps)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.07,0:06:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(Langdon sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-Back to anagrams?\N-Back to nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.66,0:06:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, a cipher was used\Nto alter the Hebrew,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,likely one with...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Masonic characteristics\Nor themes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.12,0:06:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I j... I just cannot\Nfigure out what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:07:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe it's related\Nto the Solomon story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When Dad talked\Nabout the Masons,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he always said it was\Na beautiful system of morality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.97,0:07:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-veiled in allegory.\N-Veiled in allegory, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.97,0:07:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in there,\Nhiding in plain sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.56,0:07:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-(pouring tea)\N-I should be able to see it,\Nbut I... can't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.56,0:07:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(sets teakettle down)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(takes deep breath)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.19,0:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.94,0:07:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-No.\N-My-my brain, it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.69,0:07:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it can't work if I'm\Nconstantly worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's very sweet,\Nbut I'm not gonna let this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.74,0:07:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me that I can't participate\Nin saving my own dad's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But... we're not gonna save him\Nif I can't work this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.75,0:07:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-We are going to work this out,\NLangdon.\N-Katherine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.83,0:07:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,At some point,\Nyou are going to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.87,0:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-that you actually need me,\Nyou know that?\N-You have vast knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in-in many topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.09,0:07:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Codebreaking isn't one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.05,0:07:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not my knowledge\Nthat's important, it's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The key to decoding this\Nis buried in your mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know how to dig it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.89,0:07:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,(water burbling)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.79,0:08:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's getting weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.83,0:08:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't rush the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.29,0:08:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that better\Nthan anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This things belonged to his boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They will find him in the Araf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.93,0:08:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he will see himself\Nfor who he truly is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.65,0:08:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(echoing whisper):\NWhat is the predominant wish\Nof your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Has his daughter surfaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.12,0:09:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No. She's still off the grid,\Nas far as I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If they've ignored my warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.67,0:09:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...then they must be made\Nto understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.35,0:09:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(dog barking in distance)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.94,0:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,(quietly):\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.37,0:09:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.96,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, that's so sweet.\NYou got me cannolis?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.21,0:09:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.05,0:09:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,(chuckles)\NWe're hugging.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.30,0:09:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on inside.\NDid you get a new EV?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.51,0:09:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-That looks great.\NHow many miles are you getting?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.93,0:09:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.22,0:10:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.10,0:10:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(quietly):\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.57,0:10:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.78,0:10:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And why am I sneaking you\Nlab equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-disguised as baked goods?\N-I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.57,0:10:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I know\Nhow this is gonna sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.16,0:10:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but the less you know\Nthe better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.25,0:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's fine. I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I'm just really pressed\Nfor time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't thank you enough\Nfor coming
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.34,0:10:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-all the way out here.\N-Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.84,0:10:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll call you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.42,0:10:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)\NIt's your name on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.38,0:10:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, do me a favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.43,0:10:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Say goodbye to the complete\Nstranger that just hugged me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.10,0:10:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(mouths)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.36,0:10:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this thing do, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.28,0:10:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It lets Katherine reprogram the\Nparts in me she doesn't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, that requires\Nmuch more equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With all the cryptographic data\Nyou've absorbed over your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.96,0:11:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a question\Nof having the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.96,0:11:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We know it's in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just\Ntoo much other noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,With auditory stimuli that\Ncan boost neurological activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.01,0:11:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we can elicit your\Nfrequency following response,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.18,0:11:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,drown out that noise\Nand find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.64,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be best\Nif we had a closed environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.47,0:11:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.\NSure, I'll leave y'all to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.52,0:11:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.48,0:11:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lie back. Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Interconnecting our energies\Nwill help you relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to the beats,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.17,0:11:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to the sound of my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.21,0:11:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Inhale slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.51,0:11:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. And exhale.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrate on your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They're warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.52,0:12:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let that warmth flow up\Nthrough your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it does...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,feel your body growing heavy\Nas well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you feel your body\Nbecome heavier
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,feel yourself sinking\Ninto the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.21,0:12:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...being enveloped\Nby the warmth beneath...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...being delivered\Nto a new place...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,where all of your knowledge\Nand experience reside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(inhales)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.41,0:13:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(exhales)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.25,0:13:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.58,0:13:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,(groans softly)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.94,0:13:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(three echoing knocks)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.41,0:13:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN (echoing):\NWho asks for admission here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.62,0:13:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN 2:\NA poor candidate\Nin a state of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the predominant wish\Nof your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.77,0:14:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Zachary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ZACH:\NI solemnly promise
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.24,0:14:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and swear that I will\Nnever reveal the secret arts
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and hidden mysteries belonging
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.66,0:14:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to Free and Accepted Masons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.66,0:14:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I knowingly violate\Nthis oath,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.66,0:14:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect no less penalty than\Nto have my throat cut across,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,my tongue torn out by its roots
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-No.\N-and my body buried\Nin the rough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-No!\N-(blood spatters)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(faint gasping)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.68,0:14:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.72,0:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,(exhales)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.53,0:15:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,MAL'AKH (voice-over):\NThe secret is how to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\NTell me the words\Nas they come to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.31,0:15:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Amulet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.69,0:15:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.86,0:15:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.24,0:15:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.08,0:15:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.09,0:16:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.76,0:16:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.59,0:16:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.43,0:16:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't make me do\Nanything embarrassing, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,bark like a dog or...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.43,0:16:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,rap?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.60,0:16:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Close.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"Lo, I have given thee\Na wise and understanding heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.58,0:16:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I need to see a Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.58,0:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasps) Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.79,0:16:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,(indistinct chatter)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.29,0:16:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.67,0:16:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN:\NOh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.51,0:16:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hmm?\N-Would you mind watching\Nmy stuff for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.84,0:16:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-I have to...\N-Oh, yeah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.72,0:16:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-Unless you're about to leave.\N-No, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.47,0:16:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I'm gonna be here\Nfor a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.56,0:16:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.90,0:17:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thank you.\N-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.87,0:17:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever altered the Bible text\Nreplaced some of the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.37,0:17:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In First Kings, God gave Solomon\Na wise and understanding heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,making him\Nthe legendary ruler of myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But here\Nthat script was changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It no longer reads
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.80,0:17:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"wise and understanding heart."\NIt just reads "wisdom."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.51,0:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's supposed to help you\Nunscramble the letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.89,0:17:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what's known\Nas a keyword cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It works like this. Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull the letters of "wisdom"\Nout of the alphabet
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.73,0:17:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and place them at the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hebrew transliteration\Ngoes here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you translate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.74,0:17:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"I" becomes "B."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.74,0:17:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"T" becomes "U."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"P" is "R."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,(mumbling)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:17:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"D."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.34,0:18:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"D."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.38,0:18:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\N"Buried... Ezra...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.05,0:18:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dove."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.43,0:18:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean anything to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-No.\N-Sounds like a '90s grunge band.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.43,0:18:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I haven't always been\Nthe most supportive
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.81,0:18:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of you and your work,\Nbut this was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.98,0:18:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-It was...\N-Science.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, like you said,\NI had the...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,words all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.74,0:18:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit while you're ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,NUÑEZ:\NSo, big surprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.82,0:18:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,not a grunge band.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezra Dove's a Freemason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,LANGDON:\NEzra Dove.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.04,0:18:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Died 1848.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Buried at Oaken Hill...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Cemetery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.79,0:18:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe the capstone's buried\Nwith him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,(dogs barking in distance)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.38,0:18:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up, man? How you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.81,0:19:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You having fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.52,0:19:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.94,0:19:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe instead of...\Nhanging outside my house,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be out trying to find\Nthe guy who shot up the Capitol?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed one of your guys, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\Nyou're out here harassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.82,0:19:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm not harassing you.\N-Yes, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.49,0:19:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're spying on me and my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.03,0:19:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm making you\Nuncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a cop, too. Yeah,\NI fought for this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.16,0:19:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a victim here. Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.62,0:19:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Check this out. Let me show you\Nsomething right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.92,0:19:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It came through here\Nand here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what that's called\Nis a through and through,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got cream from the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.80,0:19:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get back there\Nsometimes. It's difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.67,0:19:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you could help me\Nrub it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you\Nshould go back inside, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.72,0:19:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you go to the bathroom\Nin here, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.60,0:19:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, CIA give you\Na special bottle or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.95,0:20:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,BLAKE:\NHe's keeping his vow of silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.54,0:20:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,TRISH:\NHe's Peter's good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.63,0:20:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If he knew where to find him,\Ndon't you think he'd tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.96,0:20:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,BLAKE:\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.67,0:20:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that his group has\Ndifferent priorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.55,0:20:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the Masons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.55,0:20:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A group within the Masons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.05,0:20:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Leviathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.72,0:20:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-appointed guardians\Nof the wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.06,0:20:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is everything\Nthat we know about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.65,0:20:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw this symbol\Nin the Capitol basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the room Peter Solomon had\Ndown there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.07,0:20:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why you had\Nhis phone tapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you been looking\Nfor this portal thing, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.08,0:20:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long enough, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.04,0:20:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise I'd have\Nmore information than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.08,0:20:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why\Nyou're gonna go in there
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.16,0:20:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're gonna get more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With your keen eye\Nfor pressure points
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.59,0:20:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and your mutual connections\Nto the Solomon offspring,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.09,0:20:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I suspect that you're gonna\Ncrack him without much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.93,0:21:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So put aside regrets...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.64,0:21:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and do what you do best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(loud, indistinct chatter)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.94,0:21:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-(horn honks)\N-I can't believe this.\NIt's bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.90,0:21:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand\Nwhat you want from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.78,0:21:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was here the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.53,0:21:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even know Ahmad\Nhad left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.20,0:21:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,(laughs):\NNone of this is my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.62,0:21:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From where I stand, I'm afraid\Nthat's not entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.62,0:21:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go on a three-day\Nbender with a Saudi prince
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.50,0:21:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he drives his Ferrari\Ninto a telephone pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.79,0:21:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,high on coke you provided,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't really matter\Nwhere you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.80,0:21:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly not to his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.97,0:21:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The embassy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.68,0:21:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I have an office there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.10,0:21:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm here to help, Zach.\N-Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.02,0:21:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can help me\Nget in touch with my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.64,0:21:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a lawyer\Nwho can fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't kill me first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.81,0:21:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there was a way\Nfor you to take care of this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.27,0:21:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,without your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.90,0:22:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.57,0:22:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.12,0:22:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.83,0:22:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You made connections\Nthat could be useful to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.00,0:22:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just means going\Nwhere I tell you for a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.75,0:22:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and keeping a clean nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.67,0:22:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.01,0:22:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,including your father, needs\Nto know anything about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.97,0:22:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of gotten to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.97,0:22:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where I-I can't work\Nanywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.31,0:22:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm a bit superstitious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.56,0:22:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're a writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.11,0:22:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilty, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.86,0:22:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Would I know\Nanything you've written?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.99,0:22:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if I told you my pen name,\Nyou know, possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.12,0:22:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But I barely know you, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.83,0:22:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in superstition, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.75,0:22:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you believe in superstition?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.96,0:22:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously,\Nthere is a whole section
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.83,0:22:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-in my dissertation\Ndedicated to...\N-Dissertation?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:22:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, my God.\N-In what field?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.17,0:23:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, it's called noetic science.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.76,0:23:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mm-hmm.\N-I'm a research assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.80,0:23:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are looking for proof\Nof parapsychological phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.89,0:23:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's\Nthe mind-body connection,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.06,0:23:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole spiritual healing\Ngamut.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.35,0:23:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah.\N-Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.06,0:23:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The book I'm writing\Nis all about parapsychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.27,0:23:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-I swear to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.90,0:23:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You-you wouldn't happen\Nto know Katharine Solomon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.11,0:23:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by any chance, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.94,0:23:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.03,0:23:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, actually-- she's my boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.07,0:23:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-She's your boss?\N-Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.20,0:23:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-Get out of town.\N-(laughs)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.66,0:23:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw her earlier today,\Nin fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.12,0:23:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-You saw her today?\N-(laughs): Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.16,0:23:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.13,0:23:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I... you know, I've just\Nread a lot of her work,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.00,0:23:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-doing research\Nfor my latest book.\N-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.09,0:23:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She did this study\Non indigo children.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.05,0:23:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.09,0:23:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I assisted that study.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.93,0:23:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-No way.\N-Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.10,0:23:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I buy you\Nanother cup of coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.93,0:23:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-I mean, if you have time,\Nof course.\N-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.64,0:23:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.77,0:24:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how about a glass of wine\Ninstead?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'd love that. Yeah, sure.\N-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.11,0:24:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-MAL'AKH: Oh, my...\N-Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.78,0:24:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot believe\NI just did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.91,0:24:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm... I am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.78,0:24:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing. I'll just...\NI'm gonna go clean up quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.33,0:24:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'll be right back.\N-Needless to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.79,0:24:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-the wine's on me.\N-Okay. Deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.85,0:24:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\NWe're gonna need to find a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.48,0:24:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This place is huge.\NHe could be buried anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN:\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.32,0:24:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.70,0:24:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We're looking\Nfor someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.95,0:24:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone... dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.95,0:24:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.20,0:24:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\NOur grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.00,0:24:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We drove all the way\Nfrom Marblehead to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.87,0:24:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Sean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.17,0:25:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I, Sean,\Nand, uh, my wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.42,0:25:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.21,0:25:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...sister and I\Nw-would love to pay our respects
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.22,0:25:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to, um, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.72,0:25:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still hard for him\Nto talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.30,0:25:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pain never leaves a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.97,0:25:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why we build monuments\Nto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.35,0:25:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we didn't, you'd\Nbe standing on a golf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.10,0:25:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(chuckles):\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.15,0:25:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find the directory\Nto the grounds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.36,0:25:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,off the path to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.94,0:25:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thank you. Thanks, Father.\N-KATHERINE: Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.04,0:25:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is. But hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.08,0:25:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Uh, the code said "buried."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.08,0:25:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This says he's in section Y09,\Nwhich is the columbarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.25,0:25:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's not buried at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.51,0:25:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.40,0:26:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.93,0:26:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(footsteps continue)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.29,0:27:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.33,0:27:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna push that button.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.13,0:27:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're gonna tell me\Nwhat I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.09,0:27:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Your boss doesn't like getting\Nhis hands dirty?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.97,0:27:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So he leaves that to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.01,0:27:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Essentially, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.22,0:27:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But he and I don't always see\Neye to eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.52,0:27:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(low, rapid beeping)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.19,0:27:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(beeping stops)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.19,0:27:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(clicking)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.95,0:27:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an A80\Nshort-range EMP generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.53,0:27:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I just shorted out the cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.03,0:27:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon\Nthey'll bring new ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.58,0:27:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but whatever happens before then\Nis completely between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.08,0:27:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't care\Nabout finding some portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.13,0:27:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to find\Nyour friend Peter Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.21,0:27:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,CIA doesn't generally involve\Nitself in missing persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.47,0:28:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a personal interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.10,0:28:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,His son Zachary was\None of our assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.27,0:28:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know because I recruited him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.90,0:28:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first time I'd worked\Nwith someone so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.57,0:28:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.66,0:28:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he could handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.58,0:28:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was thrown into prison\Nfor trafficking,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.04,0:28:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ordered to disavow\Nany knowledge of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.05,0:28:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To burn him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.09,0:28:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.60,0:28:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.73,0:28:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You think finding Peter\Nwill make everything all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.06,0:28:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.28,0:28:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it'd be a start.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.24,0:29:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.16,0:29:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't know anything\Nabout the man who took him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.75,0:29:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what he's after.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.46,0:29:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If I understand that,\NI can understand him,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.54,0:29:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and that might be the difference\Nbetween Peter living and dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.44,0:29:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Section Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.40,0:29:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,LANGDON:\NThere he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.69,0:29:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-Make sure no one comes in.\N-Whoa, whoa,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.53,0:29:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-what are you doing?\N-(chuckles): Don't worry,\NI got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.78,0:29:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Tight spaces are one thing;\Nheights I can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.45,0:29:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,KATHERINE:\NWhy would somebody hide
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.58,0:29:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a capstone in an urn anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.41,0:29:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Many cultures have superstitions\Nabout desecrating human remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.21,0:29:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in of them, of\Ncourse. But a strong deter...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.67,0:29:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,(both gasp)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.26,0:30:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.13,0:30:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.63,0:30:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want me to believe\Nyou're not superstitious?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was worried about the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.81,0:30:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.35,0:30:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.65,0:30:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.20,0:30:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing in here but ash.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.24,0:30:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-(vehicle approaching)\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.29,0:30:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not our only problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.21,0:30:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone knows we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.54,0:30:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-Who?\N-Doesn't matter. We have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.71,0:30:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone's trying to stop us,\Nthat means
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.42,0:30:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we're on the right track.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.72,0:30:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The capstone\Nmust be here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.14,0:30:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-What are you doing?\N-Buying time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.89,0:30:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-(key clatters)\N-Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.10,0:30:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-Apologies again. I'm...\N-Oh, my God. It's all good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.10,0:30:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thank you for the wine.\N-Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.11,0:31:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To the mind-body connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.40,0:31:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-Cheers.\N-Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.53,0:31:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(laughs softly)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.12,0:31:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have\Na confession to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.29,0:31:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.84,0:31:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew exactly who you were\Nwhen I sat down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.43,0:31:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(laughs):\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.77,0:31:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.28,0:31:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You should probably go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.91,0:31:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,(distorted, echoing exhale)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.17,0:32:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,(distorted, echoing voices)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.36,0:32:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(distorted jingling of keys)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.19,0:32:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,(distorted, echoing breaths)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.37,0:32:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(echoing):\NEasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.50,0:32:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.67,0:32:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,(panting)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.38,0:32:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's got to be\Nsomething we're not seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.47,0:32:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, um, buried, not buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.97,0:32:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,14 letters.\NWisdom. Kings. Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.35,0:32:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He's almost here,\Nand you locked us in!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.27,0:33:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.48,0:33:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.65,0:33:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.99,0:33:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Langdon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.40,0:33:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Buried Dove.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.37,0:33:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,(door rattling)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.45,0:33:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Langdon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.29,0:33:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In Hebrew, Jonah means "dove."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.21,0:33:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Langdon!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.38,0:33:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.34,0:33:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,These reliefs tell the story\Nof Jonah and the Whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.51,0:33:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Get down!\N-And what's another word\Nfor "whale"?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.51,0:33:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Leviathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.51,0:33:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-(Langdon coughing)\N-Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.23,0:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,(coughing):\NThere's something in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.36,0:33:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh. Oh, my God.\N-(Katherine strains)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.94,0:33:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.36,0:33:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(Katherine gasps, coughs)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.90,0:33:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.91,0:33:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-It's not the capstone.\N-Just take it and keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.45,0:34:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,(both coughing)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.63,0:34:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasping breaths)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.50,0:34:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,(coughing)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.55,0:34:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,(panting):\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.39,0:34:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.51,0:34:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(thuds, creaks)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.94,0:34:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(Katherine strains,\Ncoughs loudly)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.61,0:34:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jonah get out again?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.82,0:34:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,(panting):\NGod commanded it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.74,0:34:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now would be a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.78,0:34:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(grunts loudly)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.62,0:34:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.63,0:34:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,(engine starts)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.05,0:34:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,(tires squeal)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.52,0:35:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,(insects trilling)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.69,0:35:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,(dialing)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.82,0:35:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-(line ringing)\N-(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.53,0:35:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, Lace.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.99,0:35:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.61,0:35:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.\NI'm sorry. It's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.86,0:35:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, no, all good.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.62,0:35:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got out today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.99,0:35:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, listen, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.58,0:35:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you, uh,\Nyou got anything on the shooter?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.92,0:35:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, I know, the CIA got\Nsome "eyes only" bullshit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.96,0:35:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but... we got him on camera,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.05,0:35:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So run him through Clearview,\Nget me a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.05,0:35:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, tomorrow works fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.97,0:35:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, man. I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.56,0:35:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,(chuckles)\NAll right, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.89,0:35:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,go back to watching bowling\Nor whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.23,0:35:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(car engine starts)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.69,0:35:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.74,0:35:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,(radio static)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.16,0:35:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,WOMAN (over scanner):\N...all units in vicinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.95,0:36:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Code 1, Adams Memorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.83,0:36:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonresponsive female,\Nyet to be identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.50,0:36:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Black and red SUV\Nfound at scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.92,0:36:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-Huh.\N-Maryland license\Nplate number...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.67,0:36:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,(clicks off scanner)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.92,0:36:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.68,0:36:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,brought me\Ninto the Leviathan Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.60,0:36:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the one who revealed\Nits purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.93,0:36:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All Masons tell stories\Nabout deeply held secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.81,0:36:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them are tall tales\Nto intrigue new members.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.15,0:36:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But this was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.12,0:36:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,(voice-over):\NI saw in these men
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.24,0:36:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a belief...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.12,0:36:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in something beyond possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.79,0:36:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A belief
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.75,0:36:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ancient wisdom\Nwas not only real,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.09,0:36:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but that it could\Nunlock consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.51,0:36:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing man to access
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.01,0:37:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden reservoirs of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.93,0:37:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The group was formed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.60,0:37:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,based on two questions:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.65,0:37:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Could humanity handle\Nsuch an evolution?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.82,0:37:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And what might happen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.98,0:37:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if this power fell\Ninto the wrong hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.99,0:37:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,(voice-over):\NWe made a pact
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to safeguard the clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.96,0:37:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the lure of the myth\Nwas strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.92,0:37:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.81,0:37:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a story
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.02,0:37:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of a member of the group
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.19,0:37:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the beginning\Nof the last century
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.19,0:37:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for whom the lure was too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.24,0:38:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He abandoned his oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.28,0:38:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He sought the wisdom\Nfor himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.66,0:38:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.71,0:38:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that he learned\Nto control things,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.25,0:38:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that he could bend\Nmatter to his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.30,0:38:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.24,0:38:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasps) Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.92,0:38:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(turns off projector)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.18,0:39:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,(takes deep breath)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.28,0:39:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I did an EMP gambit\Nin Frankfurt in '09.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.37,0:39:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.79,0:39:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd use a garage door opener.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.21,0:39:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,(soft chuckle)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.83,0:39:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,SATO:\NWhat do you want to do with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.67,0:39:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,BLAKE:\NCut him loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.76,0:39:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you've bonded,\Nyou can use him as needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.02,0:39:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(Langdon sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.40,0:39:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,(phone buzzes)
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.32,0:40:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.70,0:40:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it him?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.32,0:40:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quote from the Apocrypha.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourth Book of the Maccabees.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.42,0:40:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,(voice-over):\N"For if you dispose me to anger
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.30,0:40:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"by your disobedience...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.92,0:40:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"you will compel me,\Nwith dreadful punishments...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.26,0:40:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"...to destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.43,0:40:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,every one of you."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.85,0:40:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.38,0:41:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.45,0:41:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,* *
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.53,0:42:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,* *